  "prompt": "What is the best free webDAV service?",
  "response": "As of my last update, there isn't a definitive \"best\" free WebDAV service as it often depends on individual needs such as storage capacity, ease of use, security features, and compatibility with other tools. However, a few popular options were often recommended:\n\n1. **Box**: Offers WebDAV support and is known for its user-friendly interface and integration capabilities. The free plan has limited storage, which might be a constraint for some users.\n\n2. **Yandex.Disk**: Provides a WebDAV access option and offers a reasonable amount of free storage. It is relatively easy to set up and use.\n\n3. **4shared**: Supports WebDAV protocol and offers a basic free version with limited storage space.\n\n4. **MyDrive**: A lesser-known option that might not have as many features as Box but provides free storage and WebDAV access.\n\n5. **OpenDrive**: Offers WebDAV support with a free plan that includes limited storage and bandwidth.\n\nKeep in mind that service offerings and features can change frequently, so it\u2019s always a good idea to check the latest terms and user reviews before committing to a platform. Additionally, consider the privacy policies and data security measures of these services to ensure they meet your requirements.",
